
/*
 * The provided Hyperlambda code checks if an [offset] argument exists within [.arguments]. If it does, it appends an "offset" clause to an existing SQL query stored in [.sql] using [strings.concat]. The [set-value] slot updates [.sql] with the modified query. 
 * 
 * 1. [if] - Checks if the [offset] argument exists.
 * 2. [exists] - Evaluates the presence of [offset] in [.arguments].
 * 3. [.lambda] - Executes the following code if [exists] is true.
 * 4. [set-value] - Updates the value of [.sql].
 * 5. [strings.concat] - Concatenates strings to form the new SQL query.
 * 6. [get-value] - Retrieves the current SQL query and the [offset] value.
 */
if
   exists:x:@.arguments/*/offset
   .lambda
      set-value:x:@.sql
         strings.concat:x:@.sql
            get-value:x:@.sql
            .:" offset "
            get-value:x:@.arguments/*/offset
